# ⛓️ Simple TypeScript Blockchain

A lightweight, educational blockchain implementation in TypeScript demonstrating core concepts like Proof of Work, cryptographic hashing, and blockchain validation.

## 🎯 Purpose

This project was built to understand the fundamental mechanics behind blockchain technology. It implements a minimal yet functional blockchain featuring:

- SHA-256 cryptographic hashing
- Proof of Work mining with adjustable difficulty
- Blockchain validation
- Tampering detection

> **Note:** This project is intended for educational purposes only. It is not production-ready and focuses on simplicity and readability without relying on blockchain frameworks.

---

# 🚀 Getting Started

## Prerequisites

- Node.js 18 or later
- npm or yarn

## Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/blockchain-ts.git

cd blockchain-ts

# Install dependencies
npm install
```

## Running the Project

### Development Mode

```bash
npm run dev
```

### Build & Run

```bash
# Compile TypeScript
npm run build

# Execute compiled JavaScript
npm start
```

## Running Tests

```bash
# Run all tests
npm test

# Watch mode
npm run test:watch

# Coverage report
npm run test:coverage
```

---

# 💡 How It Works

## Mining (Proof of Work)

Each block must produce a hash that begins with a configurable number of leading zeros. The miner repeatedly increments the nonce until a valid hash is found.

```typescript
// Difficulty 4 means hash must start with "0000"

Target: 0000xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
Valid:  0000a1b2c3d4e5f6...
Invalid: 1234a1b2c3d4e5f6...
```

## Chain Validation

Whenever a new block is added, the blockchain verifies that:

- Every block's hash matches its contents.
- Every block correctly references the previous block.
- The blockchain has not been modified.

